description:
&lt;p&gt;Trust Temps are looking for experienced Band 5 staff nurses with robust clinical knowledge, experience working in an acute hospital environment and a proactive and adaptable approach to work. We have work available in general medicine, acute medicine, surgery and care of the elderly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer the flexibility of being able to choose the shifts you work via our online booking system and also offer excellent rates of pay &amp; weekly pay.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will provide; &lt;br /&gt;• support from our Clinical Lead in your development&lt;br /&gt;• flexible working patterns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hospital information;&lt;br /&gt;Barking, Havering and Redbridge University Hospitals NHS Trust brings together many of the country&#39;s leading experts in caring for patients across two sites in East London both of which are less than 30 minutes from Central London; King George Hospital in Goodmayes and Queen’s Hospital in Romford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If shortlisted, you will be invited to attend the Trust for testing, interview and to have your I.D documentation taken and relevant forms completed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Alison Moore Job title: Recruitment Advisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email addressalison.moore40@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01708 435000 ext 2851&lt;/p&gt;
